**Providing Comfort**
A diagnosis of dementia is frightening for both the person affected and for their loved ones.  Taking care of one's own emotional and physical health is essential. And, providing as much reassurance and comfort to the person diagnosed with dementia is crucial to their overall well-being. Here are some things that members of a care circle can do to help support the dementia patient.

1. Use a calm, natural voice. Noise and 
keep home environment calm and minimize visits to oud or unstructured environments
Listen actively
Allow comfort objects, stories, even if they seem out of character for your loved ones age
Create a memory book recordable memory book, recordable song book
photo album
